@page "/"
@using Portfolio.Components.Generic

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<section id="hero">

    <div id="pfp" class="m-2" />

    <h1>Lucas Arroyo</h1>
    <h6>Full Stack Developer</h6>

    <AppButton OnClick="@(() => Navigate("#about"))" Text="About me" Class="pt-3" />

</section>

<section id="about">

    <h2>About me</h2>

    <p>
        Hey! I'm <strong>Lucas</strong>, a Full Stack Developer based in Zaragoza, Spain.
        I consider myself a creative and proactive person, passionate about technology
        and always looking to learn something new.
    </p>

    <p>
        My favourite stack revolves around the <strong>.NET ecosystem</strong>,
        with a particular focus on <strong>ASP.NET</strong>, especially
        <strong>Blazor</strong>, and <strong>SQL Server</strong>.
        That said, I'm always happy to step outside my comfort zone and work
        with technologies such as <strong>Angular</strong>, <strong>Java</strong>,
        or whatever the project calls for.
    </p>

    <p>
        In 2023, I had the chance to join the <strong>Erasmus+ programme</strong>
        and intern at <a href="https://www.continero.com/en/" target="_blank">Continero</a>
        in Brno, Czech Republic, an experience that pushed me to grow a lot both
        professionally and personally.
    </p>

    <p>
        Since then, I've kept building, learning and taking on new challenges,
        working on real-world projects across different industries and always
        looking for ways to improve my habilities.
    </p>

    <p>
        When I'm not coding, you'll probably find me working on music. I love
        recording, producing and experimenting with new ideas, mainly in the
        <strong>pop</strong> genre. It's one of my favourite ways to stay creative,
        learn new things and enjoy the process of turning an idea into something real.
    </p>

